President Obama has nominated Willie Lee Richardson, Jr. to be the United States Marshal for the Middle District of Georgia. Richardson currently serves as a Supervisory Criminal Investigator in the United States Marshals Service. President Obama praised Richardson's distinguished career in public safety and expressed gratitude for his service. Richardson has been employed with the United States Marshals Service since 1989 and previously worked for the Lowndes County Sheriff's Office in Georgia. He holds an Associate's Degree in Applied Science from the Community College of the Air Force and served in the United States Air Force from 1981 to 1985.